directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, sugar and baking powder in separate bowl.
Mix egg with milk; add to dry ingredients.
(May need more milk it batter is too thick.)
Beat until smooth.
Hold finger over bottom of a funnel and pour in some batter.
Remove finger and let batter drop in a spiral motion into pan filled with 1-inch hot oil (375°).
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Remove from pan and drain on a paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup and rotel tomatoes to ground beef and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Layer ground beef mixture, corn tortillas, and cheese in baking dish.
Top with more grated cheese.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: tex-mex bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine corn chips, water and eggs. Press into 9 inch pie plate or casserole.
Bake for 10 minutes. Brown ground chuck, drain.

title: mo's dream bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan, then sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Press crust to smooth.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crust.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down firmly.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: simple potato salad
directions: Peel, cube and boil potatoes until tender.
Strain and place in a bowl.
Add all other ingredients.
Toss and serve.

title: dutch babies
directions: Put margarine in 6 custard cups.
Combine 3 eggs, flour, milk, oil and almond extract and put into cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Remove to dessert dishes.
Melt marmalade and add to fruit to coat.
Put fruit into Dutch Babies and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture and mix well.

title: pork chops and lima beans
directions: Cook lima beans in salty water until tender.
Brown pork chops.
Make sauce of other ingredients.
Put pork chops and lima beans in Dutch oven.
Pour over the sauce.
Cook slowly on top of stove for 30 minutes.

title: cherry red hot jello
directions: Mix jello, water and red hots together and cool. Add apples and nuts. Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pork chops and corn casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Spray your casserole pan with Pam and pour in mixture just made.
Brown pork chops and place on top of mixture; bake for 30 minutes at 375° or until brown.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish so pieces don't overlap. Cover with mushrooms.
Combine mushroom soup, sherry and sour cream.
Stir until blended.
Pour over chicken, completely covering it.
Dust with paprika.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Then add flour, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 15 minutes.
Roll thin in sugar and cinnamon before baking.

title: good potato soup
directions: Cook bacon and onion in 4 quart Dutch oven, drain and place on paper towels.
Place potatoes, celery, carrots, water and salt in Dutch oven.
Cover and cook over high heat until it comes to a boil, about 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Drain in colander.
Place half the potatoes in blender, puree until smooth.
Return puree mixture, remaining potato mixture, bacon and onions back in Dutch oven.
Stir in cream, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil.
Place in serving bowls and sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken and remove from pan.
Brown onions and garlic. Combine all the rest of the ingredients.
Add chicken, onions and garlic; simmer 45 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in wine.

title: fried chicken breast
directions: Cut chicken into small strips.
Dip chicken into pancake and buttermilk mixture.
Put oil and butter in pan and heat.
Lay strips of chicken in pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; set aside.
Cream together butter and sugars; add beaten eggs.
Add flour mixture, mixing well.
Roll into small balls and flatten somewhat with a fork.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: meatball fondue
directions: Add water to pineapple juice can to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Stir in other ingredients until bubbly.
Put in fondue pot.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: noodles
directions: Mix together; roll on floured surface.
Cut to desired thickness.
Boil beef, chicken or any type broth.
Add noodles, let stand about 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening thoroughly.
Add the sugars, eggs, vanilla and peanut butter.
Gradually add flour, soda and salt. Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Flatten to 1/4 inch. Bake at 400° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain well.
In large pan, combine tomatoes, rice, corn, mixed vegetables and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently, to prevent sticking.
Add hamburger mixture; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
May be frozen.
Very good!

title: spring rolls
directions: Heat vegetable oil in frying pan.
Add chopped garlic and fry for 2 minutes.
Put in ground pork, shrimp, crab meat, bean sprouts, eggs, green onion, celery, black mushrooms and jelly noodles.
Fry for 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce, nampla, salt and pepper

title: country house brownies
directions: Melt
butter in saucepan;
cool.
Add brown sugar, egg, salt, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix well; add chocolate	chips (coconut
and
nuts optional).
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.	Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs. Add other ingredients and bake in a 325° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: edible peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix and knead into a pliable dough, adding more powdered sugar, if necessary.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Use powdered sugar for "flour" for rolling.
Can be pressed into a shallow pan as "candy."

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix together crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press equal portions into paper lined muffin cups. In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Spoon equal amounts of mixture (about 3 tablespoons) into prepared cups.
Bake for 20 minutes or until set; cool.
Chill.
Top with filling.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease a 10 1/2 inch cast iron skillet with 1 Tbsp. vegetable oil. Sprinkle corn meal over oil and let it brown slightly. Combine next 5 ingredients in a bowl, stirring well. Pour half of corn meal mixture into skillet. Sprinkle with 1 c. cheese, ground beef and peppers. Top with remaining corn meal mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add oil. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add dry ingredients alternately to first mixture.
Add lemon extract, raisins and pecans.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat chocolate and water until chocolate is completely melted.
Mix margarine and sugar until fluffy; add egg yolks. Stir in chocolate and water mixture and flour and buttermilk; mix until smooth.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Pour into wax paper-lined 1-inch round pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apricot ribbon salad
directions: Heat nectar to boiling.
Remove from heat and add jello, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture; set aside.
Divide remaining gelatin in half. Pour half into 2-quart mold.
Refrigerate until set.
Keep other half at room temperature.

title: champagne chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice and thyme and let marinate for 5 minutes.
Then season with salt and pepper.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make into balls and fry in skillet with 1 large jar Welch's grape jelly and 1 1/2 bottles of chili sauce.
Put into casserole dish; bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: squash casserole
directions: *Chop and cook onion with squash until done; drain and cool.

title: strawberry cream dressing
directions: Place ingredients in a food processor.
Process until smooth and creamy.
Serve over fresh fruit.
Thin with milk, slightly, to serve as a soup.
Refrigerate, covered; dressing will keep up to 3 days.
Makes 1 cup.

title: oreo cookies
directions: Cream shortening and eggs together.
Add cake mixes.
Roll into 1-inch balls and cook 10 minutes at 350°.
When cookies have cooled, add filling between.

title: hot fruit dish
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Melt butter; add sugar and curry powder.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: lime punch
directions: Spoon ice cream and sherbet into 6-quart punch bowl.
Pour juice and Sprite over ice cream and sherbet.
This is so easy to make and so good.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: granny's watergate salad
directions: Stir jello into Cool Whip until well dissolved.
Drain can of pineapple and stir in.
Next, stir in rest of ingredients and chill.

title: strawberry pie(sugar-free)
directions: In saucepan, stir together pudding mix and jello with water; stir over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Cool in refrigerator until thick.
Arrange strawberries in pie shell. Pour mixture over berries.
Chill until set.
Serve with "Sweet Pretenders" sugar-free topping.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Place eggs, dark corn syrup, peanut butter and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in peanuts; mix well.
Pour batter into pie crust.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1
hour. Cool and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and microwave about 5 minutes until warm. Pour over chicken or ribs.
Place in oven and cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper, garlic salt, basil and oregano; drain.
Add soup and 1 can of water.

title: cheddar cheese-bacon bread(bread macine recipe, 1 pound loaf)
directions: Put ingredients in order listed.
Use basic bake cycle.
After first kneading is finished, add 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup cooked, crumbled bacon.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt chips in double boiler over hot water.
Crush noodles by hand.
Add alternately with peanuts, stirring constantly.
When blended well, drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Let harden or chill 1/2 hour.
Store in airtight container.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Scald milk.
Place grated squash into prepared pie crust.
Combine milk, sugar and egg mixture together.
Add spices.
Pour over squash and bake at 350° about 1 hour or until silver knife inserted in center comes out clean. Do not let boil.

title: turkey lasagne(serves 8 to 10)
directions: In large saucepan, saute ground turkey, onion, garlic and mushrooms in oil until turkey looses pink color.
Add tomato juice, tomato paste and spices, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and salt.
In mixing bowl, beat margarine for 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter and sugars; beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add dry ingredients; beat until well combined.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar if desired.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with fork.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Put evaporated milk, chocolate morsels, marshmallows and salt into heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until chocolate and marshmallows melt completely and mixture thickens.
Take off heat and cool to room temperature.
Use a 9-inch pie pan.
Fill with a graham cracker crust or line bottom and sides of pan with vanilla wafers.
Spoon 1/2 of 1 quart vanilla ice cream over crust or wafers with 1/2 the chocolate mixture.
Repeat with rest of ice cream, then chocolate.
Top with chopped peanuts or pecans.

title: special evening cocktail
directions: Combine orange juice, rum, liqueur and ice cubes in a large jar with tight fitting lid and shake well.
Pour into 2 cocktail glasses.
Garnish with orange slices and serve immediately to your favorite man.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion; drain fat.
Add Tabasco sauce. In greased casserole dish, spread refried beans on the bottom. Spread meat and onion mixture on top of beans.
Spread green chillies next.
Spread cheese on top.
Drizzle taco sauce over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add sour cream by the spoonfuls on top of everything after it's cooled for a minute. Serve with tostados.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of a microwave safe dish, then spread chili over cream cheese.
Top with grated cheese.
Microwave on high 2-4 minutes or until cheese melts and chili bubbles.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry rhubarb salad
directions: Cool all together good.
You can use Sweet 'N Low in place of sugar.

title: hamburger and noodles
directions: Brown hamburger in large skillet with onion and green pepper. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Cook macaroni noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse with hot water and drain again.
Put noodles in large bowl and add margarine.
Mix.
Drain hamburger.
Squeeze out excess grease with paper towels.
Mix well in bowl with noodles.
Serve.

title: homemade soup
directions: Cook meat well.
Remove bones.
Chop up.
Add stew beef.
Set aside.
Cook potatoes, onion and sweet potatoes until tender.
Add rest of ingredients except hot pepper.
Add salt, sugar and pepper to taste.
Boil for 1 hour.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix the flour, sugar and soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast water to buttermilk and mix all at once.
Place desired amount of dough on floured cloth.
Pat out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on greased sheet and let rise.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and margarine well.
Add milk.
Mix well. Put in a double boiler and bring to boiling point.
Then add cornstarch and vanilla.
(Mix a little milk with starch and vanilla before adding to hot mixture.)
Cook until thick as desired.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Top with icing of egg whites and bake until brown.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Crush the cereal and melt the oleo.
Dip chicken in oleo and roll in the cereal.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: applesauce - raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add frozen berries and stir until thawed.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Chill until set.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish (8 x 13-inch); top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Put egg whites, sugar, water and corn syrup in upper part of double boiler and beat with eggbeater until thoroughly mixed. Cook and beat until frosting stands in peaks.
Remove from fire and add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Coconut may be added to frosting, if desired.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine using package directions and drain.
Combine all ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Chill in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, slightly beaten egg yolks and a mixture of sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon; beat 5 minutes.
Mix cream, butter and whiskey.
Beat egg whites until rounded peaks are formed. Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan. Bake at 357° for about 45 minutes or until a silver knife comes out clean when inserted halfway between center and edge of filling.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Mix eggs (do not whip) until blended.
Slice peppers lengthwise and remove seeds and stems.
Into a 16 inch pie pan place 1/2 inch layer of coarsely grated cheese.
Place peppers in a circular design around dish pointed towards center.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Pour eggs over mixture evenly.
Garnish with pimento.

title: mom's sugar cookies(good)
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar or use slotted spoon to make an interesting imprint.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.
This makes 3 dozen small cookies.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with 1/2 cup of the lemonade concentrate.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; gradually blend in crushed pineapple, followed by 1 cup pecans, green peppers, onion and salt.
Chill well.
Form into ball; roll in 1 cup pecans.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: chinese stir-fry
directions: In a wok, put butter.
Let melt and start to sizzle.
Add vegetables and Oriental noodles.
Add teriyaki marinade and seasoning.
Cover and cook until vegetables are at desired doneness.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Saute butter and onions.
Pour water over bread.
Squeeze bread dry.
Add all to ground beef mix.
Add nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls.
Roll in flour.
Brown in skillet.

title: chili-cheese squares
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Whisk in flour, butter, baking powder and onion salt until mixture is smooth.
Stir in cheeses and chilies.
Pour into greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish, square or round.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until firm and well browned.
Cut into squares or wedges.

title: cold dough cookies
directions: Combine flour, butter and Crisco and crumb the mixture as you would for pie crust.
Add egg yolks to top of flour mixture (do not mix yet; wait until ingredients are in the mix.)
Add 1/2 cup sour cream to flour mixture.
Add cake of yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and vanilla to remaining sour cream in its container.
Mix until yeast is dissolved.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture and stir by hand until dough is soft.
Place dough in airtight container overnight (covering dough with plastic bag works well.) Divide dough into 5 parts and add flour and plenty of sugar.
Roll with rolling pin to 1/8-inch thick (very thin); cut into triangles and add filling to wide section of triangle and roll as you would crescent rolls.
Roll in sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lou's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute ground turkey; drain and add crushed tomatoes, tomato sauce, paste and beer.
Season with bay leaf, oregano, basil, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, thyme, salt and pepper.
Begin this when you begin sauteing ground turkey.
Saute in olive oil, onion, celery, mushrooms and garlic.
Slowly cook all ingredients for 2 hours.
Serve over freshly cooked pasta.

title: key lime cake
directions: Combine the oil, orange juice, eggs, gelatin and the cake mix and blend well.
Pour the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Remove the cake from the oven and while it is still warm, prick the top of it all over with a fork.
Combine the lime juice and the confectioners sugar and drizzle the mixture over the cake.
(This mixture should be thin so as to penetrate the cake.)
Cut the cake into squares to serve.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Put 3 1/2 cups flour in large bowl.
Add 2 packages yeast, sugar, salt and soda and mix together.

title: chicken 'n beef
directions: Roll out chicken breasts until thin.
Cut lengthwise into 4 strips.
Roll up strips starting with small end and wrap with bacon and secure with toothpick.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup.
In a greased casserole, lay at least 1 piece of dried beef for each chicken/bacon roll.
Place roll on beef and pour cream/soup mixture over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Usually serves 6.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and peanut butter.
Add egg, vanilla and milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Roll into 1-inch balls; roll balls in sugar and bake at 375° for 8 minutes on ungreased baking sheets. Remove from sheets immediately and press chocolate kiss into each cookie.

title: pop corn balls
directions: Boil for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together.
Bring the oleo, cocoa and water or coffee to a boil and pour over flour mixture, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat together, mixing well with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: choco torte
directions: Melt oleo. Mix with flour and nuts. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool. Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 carton Cool Whip.

Spread on crust. Mix 2 packages instant pudding according to package directions. Spread over cream cheese layer. Top with other 1/2 carton Cool Whip and garnish with shaved chocolate bar. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix approximately 2 hours ahead of serving and chill.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice 1/4-inch thick. Cook slowly on top of stove in boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt. Cook until almost tender. Remove from water. Place in baking dish and add sugar, Karo, water, butter and vanilla. Bake at 400° until liquid begins to thicken and potatoes are tender. Baste occasionally while cooking.

title: asparagus-pea casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and pour into bottom of prepared baking dish. Drain peas and pour on top of asparagus.
Spoon soup over peas. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Layer vegetables in order listed in a glass baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Mix Bisquick with enough water to make it pourable. Pour over vegetable/cheese layers making sure to cover all areas. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: texas crab grass
directions: Saute onion in butter or oleo. Add spinach, crabmeat and Parmesan cheese. Serve in chafing dish with Melba rounds.

title: grasshopper bars
directions: Prepare cocoa brownies as directed.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients except chocolate.
Spread over brownies.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Heat chocolate over low heat until melted.
Spread evenly over powdered sugar mixture.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours. Cut into bars about 1 1/2 x 1-inch.
Makes 36 bars, 140 calories per bar.

title: meat pie
directions: Cook carrots and potatoes together.
Put pie shell in pie pan. Layer the ingredients into the pie shell:
Beef on bottom, onion, potatoes and carrots (drained).
Season and top with gravy.
Top pie with crust.
Bake at 375° until hot and crust is nicely browned.

title: crisco crispy fried chicken
directions: Heat Crisco oil in large nonstick skillet on medium high heat. Pour milk into shallow bowl.
Combine flour, paprika, salt, garlic powder and pepper in large plastic food bag.
Dip chicken into milk and shake one piece of chicken at a time in flour mixture to coat. Fry chicken 25 minutes or until meat near the bone is no longer pink.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix in bowl the egg, applesauce, corn, peppers, onion, jalapeno peppers and sugar.
Add corn mix.
Stir just until blended (mixture will be thick).
Pour into hot greased iron skillet.
Bake at 375° in preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes. Insert toothpick in center. Bread is done when toothpick comes out clean.

title: apricot filling for kolaches
directions: Put
apricots in pot and add just enough water to cover the apricots.
Cook
on
low
heat
about 20 or 25 minutes or until tender.
Add
sugar
and cook until sugar is dissolved; add lemon juice.
Cool well.

title: cherry pudding torte
directions: Mix flour,
sugar
and oleo.
Press into a 10 x 10-inch or 7 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven. Watch closely.
Cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cook at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool completely before removing from Bundt pan to avoid sticking.
Let cool on rack and decorate with cream cheese frosting.

title: mom eldridge's apple crisp(kelley jo's great great grandmother)
directions: Spread apples evenly in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; pour water over top.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon; stir lightly to mix and then cut butter with a pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water; add both Jell-O and gelatin together and stir.
Add syrup from oranges.
Stir.
Add sherbet and chill until partially thickened.
Fold in oranges.
Pour into mold.
Add maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: big john's cowboy beef
directions: Begin by putting a little butter or oil in skillet. Add all vegetables and cook until al dente. Add beef and cook all together until meat is browned and veggies are tender to the bite.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, evaporated milk in a large electric skillet.
Set control dial at 280°.
Bring to a fast boil; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off fry pan.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows, peanut butter are melted and blended.
Turn into a buttered 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cool before cutting in squares.

title: pink punch
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, juices and ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish punch bowl with slices of lemon or oranges.
Place a little bunch of flowers in center of each slice and let float on top of punch.

title: punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and 2 cups sugar and dissolve in 6 cups hot water. Add the pineapple juice, almond extract, lemonade concentrate and 1 cup sugar.
Blend well. Freeze in 2 milk cartons.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix bananas, marshmallows and pineapple in with jello.
Cook the following together until thick:
egg, pineapple juice, sugar and flour.
Cool and add cream cheese into the cooked mixture. Put over jello and sprinkle with nuts.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, one at a time, beating well after each one. Beat in vanilla and food coloring very slowly.
Combine flour and salt and add to creamy mixture, along with milk, mixing very slowly until mixed very well.
Bake in a greased and floured large tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Let cool. Then frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: can-can fruit punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large plastic container; cover and refrigerate.
Stir in ginger ale and serve over ice. Yields 5 quarts.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup of hot water.
Mix eggs, box cake mix, oil and lemon flavor.
Mix with dissolved Jell-O.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix vegetables, soup and chicken together.
Place into one pie shell, then put the other shell on top so that it forms the top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir.
Remove from heat and add jello until dissolved and cool. Set in refrigerator, then add buttermilk and stir until combined. Fold in Cool Whip and chopped nuts.
Spoon into dish and chill until firm.

title: ten minute vegetable soup
directions: Follow directions on the package to prepare the Ramen noodle soup in a large saucepan. Add vegetables. You may want to add water since the soup will be thicker. Let the soup come to a boil, then lower heat to a simmer. Serve hot. For added flavor, include 1 chicken flavored bouillon cube, chunks of cooked chicken, hot pepper sauce or anything else to your liking.

title: nut puffs
directions: Cream butter and sugar with vanilla.
Add flour and mix well. Stir in nuts.
Form into marble sized balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
As soon as removed from the oven, roll in confectioners sugar.
This will form a glaze.

title: taco salad(great for get-togethers)
directions: Layer everything from the top of the list down.
If you do not want meat or beans, skip these ingredients.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pour pie filling into buttered 3 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with spice, then sprinkle with cake mix, followed by pecans and melted butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake about 10 minutes longer, or until lightly browned.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Blend well. Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Combine shortening, granulated sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and water; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in butterscotch morsels and coarsely chopped nuts.
Drop by well rounded 1/2 teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on box.
Bake in 9 x 13 inch pan let cool.
Mix pudding with drained pineapple, add other ingredient and mix well.
Ice cake after cool.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Cool and add all other ingredients, except ginger ale.
Freeze until ready to serve, then add ginger ale.

title: pepsi pork roast
directions: Bake in oven at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: cheesy squares
directions: Mix cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk until really creamy. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and spread 1 package of crescent rolls on it.
Top with cream cheese mixture.
(You can add nuts or fruit on top of this.)
Top with other package crescent rolls.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Allow to cool, then cut into squares.

title: marshmallow crisp brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed in 13 x 9 inch greased baking dish. Sprinkle baked brownies with marshmallows and return to oven for 3 - 5 minutes or until melted and golden. Cool on wire rack. In a saucepan, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter over medium heat, stirring constantly until chips are melted. Remove from heat and stir in cereal. Spoon and spread evenly over marshmallows.

title: peach cobbler pie
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together.
Add milk and flour.
Stir well.
Pour dough in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour peaches and juice over dough.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup sugar.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350° or until light golden brown.
Peaches will sink to the bottom and crust will form on top.

title: soul spareribs
directions: Place ribs in large kettle.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Drain and refrigerate until ready to grill.
Mix all other ingredients. Place ribs on grill, setting 6 to 8-inches from heat.
Cook for 15 minutes; turn and brush with sauce.
Cook 15 to 30 minutes longer, turning and basting frequently.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oven baked stew beef
directions: Place stew meat in pan or baking dish.
Sprinkle onion soup on top.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over this.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Sift flour and corn meal.
Measure and add soda, cream of tartar, salt and sugar.
Sift again.
Add beaten egg, sour cream, milk and melted shortening.
Beat thoroughly.
Pour into a greased pan (9-inch) square.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: lettuce cashew salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the lettuce, bacon (crumbled), onion, cauliflower and cashews.
Mix together the salad dressing and sugar.
Put the dressing on top of the other ingredients. Reserve some of the cashews and bacon to sprinkle on top of the dressing.
Do not make too far ahead as this salad tends to get juicy.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute garlic and onions in oil until soft.
Add green peppers, eggplant and zucchini.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat, tossing well.
Add tomatoes with liquid and seasonings.
Simmer until just tender (about 30 minutes).
Cover last 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms during last 10 minutes.

title: creamy pineapple cheesecake(microwave)
directions: Spray a 9-inch pie plate with cooking spray; sprinkle with crumbs.
In blender or food processor blend yogurt, egg, sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually add cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Pour into a large microwavable bowl.
Microwave on High (100%), whisking 3 times, 8 to 10 minutes or until it looks like chilled pudding.
Remove; stir until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Top with Pineapple Topping.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add nuts and marshmallows to pineapple.
Stir in pudding. Fold in Cool Whip and cherries.
Chill and serve.

title: steamed oysters
directions: Prepare oysters as if you were going to serve them on the half shell.
Place oysters on baking sheet.
Put salt and pepper to taste on each.
Place a drop of margarine and a drop of hot sauce on each.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top of each.
Place in preheated 400° oven for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: oriental pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with Tony Chachere seasoning and dust lightly with flour.
Brown in oil in skillet with tight fitting lid. Cover chops with peppers and onions and pour soy sauce over all. Cover tightly and reduce heat.
Cook for about 25 minutes, turning once.

title: fettuccine a la didi
directions: Cook fettuccine in water and olive oil until it is tender. Set aside.
Melt butter in a frying pan and saute garlic, 1 to 2 minutes; then add spinach.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until moisture has evaporated.
Add cream and nutmeg; season with salt and pepper.
Toss in the fettuccine and Parmesan cheese; stir and cook for a final minute.
Serve with extra Parmesan cheese.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips.
Put in casserole; sprinkle potato chips over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: In a long
casserole dish pour in rice evenly.
Salt to taste. Place pieces
of
chicken
on top of rice;
salt.
Mix cream of chicken
soup
and
water.
Pour over the chicken and rice.
Lay thin
patties
of
butter on each piece of chicken. Bake at 350° until the water mixture has cooked out, approximately 45 minutes to an hour.

title: shrimp and avocado salad
directions: Note:
To prepare, 20 minutes (allow time for chilling).

title: sugarless pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: baked cornish hens
directions: Clean and dry hens.
Season inside and out with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sausage stuffed squash
directions: Wash squash thoroughly; cook in boiling salted water to cover, 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, but still firm.
Drain and cool slightly.
Trim off stems.
Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove and reserve pulp, leaving a firm shell.

title: nana chocolate squares
directions: Mix by hand (batter will be extremely thick).
Spread by hand into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: flounder amandine(microwave)
directions: Place almonds and butter in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Microwave at High 6 minutes or until almonds are lightly toasted. (Stir at 2 minute intervals).
Stir in lemon juice.
Place fillets over almonds and cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small corner of wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork, giving dish a half-turn after 4 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into two 8 x 11-inch pans.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spread on muffins.
Quarter the muffins. Freeze on cookie sheet, then place in freezer bag.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes as needed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well and put in sprayed casserole.
Top with seasoned croutons rolled (or bread crumbs) with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, onions and salt until tender.
Drain and add chicken soup, celery soup, sour cream, pimentos, salt, pepper and grated cheese (optional).
Mix stuffing mix and margarine. Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.
Put 1/2 dressing mix in bottom of dish.
Pour squash mixture in pan and top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Mix milk and flour well and set aside.
Cut up peeled potatoes and boil until tender.
Add milk and flour mixture and cook until thickens.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with cornbread muffins.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell in which strawberries have been placed.
Top with cool whip, and garnish with strawberries.

title: caramel pie
directions: Slowly brown 1/2 cup sugar in skillet.
Do not stir while it's browning.
When sugar is browned, pour about 1/2 cup warm water in and let sugar melt.
Put 3/4 cup sugar, flour, pinch of salt and milk in bowl.
Mix well and add eggs to melted sugar in skillet. Put egg yolks in cup and add some of the hot mixture before putting in skillet.
Stir until thickened and add vanilla and oleo and pour in baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar for top of pie.
Egg whites will beat better if you add a few grains of salt and pinch of baking powder.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat
oil
in large skillet and cook onions, garlic and pepper until
tender.
Add
remaining
ingredients
in
order listed, stirring well after each addition.	Simmer, uncovered, 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.	Meatballs can be added at this time and cooked for 30 minutes.	Sauce freezes well.

title: 14 carat cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat for 1 minute.
Stir in carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, shortening, eggs and salt; alternately adding dry mixture and milk.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: jambolette
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add soup, etc.
Mix in casserole with noodles and cover with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: miracle chocolate cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and slice 2 large eggplants.
Parboil in salted water. Drain and mash.
Cut 4 strips of bacon into small pieces.
Saute with onion.
Add stewed tomatoes to bacon and onion.
Crumble bread; mix all ingredients together.
Add seasoning to taste. Pour into slightly greased casserole and bake 30 minutes in preheated 325° oven.
Serve hot.

title: german rolls(zwiebacks)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar.
Mix . Let come to top, then add to flour, bacon grease and warm milk.
Stir up good. Add flour and knead to stiffness.
Let rise to top.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Squeeze off lump of dough, putting one on top of another.
Space 1-inch apart.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes until brown.

title: chop suey
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
With sharp knife, slice pork into thin and bite-size pieces.
In small bowl combine cornstarch, next 4 ingredients and 1/2 cup water; set aside.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and sliced orange, until juices are thawed.
Add ginger ale and float orange slices.
Add a few ice cubes, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Take 1 package smoked beef; chop fine.
Mix with other ingredients.
Chop 2nd package of beef and roll cheese ball in this.
Refrigerate.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Pumpkin Mixture: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, pumpkin, lemon juice, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves; mix together. Pour into greased and floured 15 x 10 cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes (your oven may be less). Dust a dish towel and roll lengthwise like a jelly roll. Let rest, then unroll. Cool approximately 2 minutes, then re-roll in towel and let cool completely.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix together cooking oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix all dry ingredients including apples and pecans.
Add first mixture to second mixture and stir.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or toothpick test.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together. Reserve 2 cups for topping.
Add eggs, buttermilk and baking soda; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan or 2 round cake pans. Add cinnamon to reserved mix.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch or 25 minutes in round pans.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions and pour off any excess grease.
Add beans, tomatoes and soup.
Layer in a large casserole dish the soft tortillas, then meat mixture, then grated cheese.
Do another 3 layers, ending with a lot of cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in 350° oven until bubbly, about 35 minutes.
Feeds approximately 20 people.

title: taco salad
directions: In pan, put refried beans; spread.
Add sour cream on top of this.
Chop up tomatoes; put on top.
Add salsa.
Break up lettuce and put on top.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: susan horton's cranberry sauce
directions: Boil water and pour over Jell-O.
Stir and add berries and cranberry sauce.
Add nuts.
Pour into a 2-quart oiled ring mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken divan
directions: Put broccoli in greased dish with chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Combine bread crumbs with butter and spread on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: carolina peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
You will need pastry for 9-inch double crust.

title: one hour yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Place the milk, sugar, butter and salt in a pan.
Heat until lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour; mix well.
Place in a greased bowl and brush the top with melted butter.
Let rise for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto a floured board.
Pat until 3/4-inch thick.
Cut into rounds with a floured biscuit cutter.
Fold the rolls over and press the edges together lightly.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Makes about 3 dozen rolls.

title: braised beef
directions: Roll beef in flour.
Brown in a skillet in a little shortening.
Place in covered dish or roaster.
Blend and add to meat the water, bouillon cubes and flour.
Dissolve bouillon cubes a little before adding to meat.
Add no salt or pepper, it's in the cubes.

title: homemade salami
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 3 days, mixing well each day.
On the fourth day, mix well and form into 5 rolls.
Bake on rack over a pan for 11 hours at 140° or 9 hours at 150°.
Turn rolls every 2 hours; cool.
Wrap and may be frozen.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix vegetables and cheeses.
Place in dish. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over top.
Place a few pats of butter or oleo on top.
Bake at 400° about 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: baked angel food delight
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip. Pour between slices. Pour gel on top; let drip over sides. Add sliced strawberries to gel.

title: diet corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into Pam-sprayed pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar and oil until fluffy.
Blend 1 egg at a time thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend a little dry ingredients with a little of milk until all gone.
Beat thoroughly.
Now mix vanilla and lemon.
Pour into tube cake pan (lightly greased).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain, flake and remove bones and skin from salmon.
Combine all except parsley and pecans.
Chill several hours.
Roll into roll.
Mix parsley and nuts and roll salmon in mix.
Chill well. Serve with favorite crackers.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil sugar, butter, syrup or molasses and salt for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add soda and flavoring.
Stir well over corn. Place in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool and store in covered container.
(I cook mine in large roasting pan.)

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan; line with honey graham crackers. Mix pudding with the milk.
Beat 2 minutes and fold in Cool Whip. Pour a layer of pudding over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers, then another layer of pudding.
Top with a layer of crackers.
Frost with Fudge Frosting.
Refrigerate.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and nutmeg; add oleo and beat until creamy.
Stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes longer.

title: my zoop
directions: Mix soup with milk.
Saute onion, celery and pepper until tender and add to soup.
Boil carrots until tender and add to soup. Saute pork chop and add to soup.
Bring to simmer and serve.
Top with Parmesan cheese and chives, if desired.
Serves 4 generously.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Stir gradually.
Stir in egg yolks; stir constantly. Put egg whites on top and brown.

title: spinach and artichoke party dip
directions: Mix sour cream and Ranch mix in medium bowl.
Add artichokes, spinach and pimentos.
Cut slice off top of round loaf and hollow out, leaving 1-inch shell.
Reserve bread pieces for dipping. Spoon dip into bread.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour.
Stir in fruit cocktail juice and all.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2 in. pan for 30 to 40 minutes.
Mix sugar, margarine, milk and flavoring, and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over cake while still warm in baking dish.

title: part low plantation cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Place in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down (crisscross design) with fork.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, using package directions; drain.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup cracker crumbs; mix well.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: bird feeders
directions: Mix ingredients together to make a putty consistency.
Drill holes in logs.
Pack mix in holes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, pepper and cheese in a saucepan over low heat until cheese is melted.
Mix with green beans and 1/2 can French-fried onions.
Put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 30 minutes or until heated through. Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes more or until onions are golden.

title: stove top cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, cocoa and butter in medium pan.
Cook on medium heat.
Cook 3 minutes after boiling.
Remove from heat. Add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture onto wax paper.
Remove when firm.

title: quick and easy meal
directions: Add onion to ground beef, salt and pepper and brown meat.
Add frozen mixed vegetables and enough water to cover mixture.
Bring to boil, then simmer with lid on until done, 20 to 25 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix ingredients together. Spoon into skillet with small amount of heated oil.
Brown on both sides.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 325° until firm and done.

title: broccoli cauliflower casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add flour, butter and cottage cheese.
Pour in casserole dish.
Layer veggies over mixture.
Cover with the Velveeta cheese strips.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 4 layer chocolate pie
directions: Melt oleo and stir in flour and nuts.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate and spread like a crust.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Set aside.
In a mixer bowl, beat sugar and shortening with electric mixer until light, scraping sides of bowl often.
Add eggs, one at a time, and the milk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add flour mixture and banana alternately to creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Fold in nuts.
Turn batter into a lightly greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pan; cool.

title: spring garden salad
directions: You can add any other veggies you choose.
The secret is to keep the pieces small.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Bake pastry shells as directed on package and cool.
Preheat oven to 300°.
In large bowl combine eggs, sour cream, Worcestershire and salt.
Blend well.
Stir in cheese, bacon and onions.
Divide mixture between 2 pie shells.
Bake in oven at 300° for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut blender pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter, and vanilla in electric blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased 9 inch pie plate.
Let stand about 5 minutes then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer potatoes with other ingredients, ending with Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: grandpa carr's best chili
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat until red is all gone.
Add onion and cook a couple of minutes.
Scrape a place in the center and cook garlic (fresh) for about 1/2 minute, then stir into meat mix. Add salt, pepper, chili powder, cumin, brown sugar, hot sauce and tomatoes.
Put cloves, allspice and bay leaf into tea ball and place in mixture.
Stir to mix well.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes.
Add kidney beans and cook 30 minutes.
Add oregano and cook 15 minutes.
Add red wine if desired.
Enjoy.

title: shake and bake
directions: Mix together.
Put in covered container in refrigerator. Makes 4 to 4 1/2 cups.
Will cover about 5 pounds of chicken.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine chopped walnuts, margarine and flour.
Put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let cool.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Grease 13x9-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onions, drain, add next six ingredients.
Simmer until liquid is evaporated. Pour 1/2 c. taco sauce into casserole dish.
Put layer of tortillas, add 1/2 c. taco sauce over tortillas.
Spoon beef mixture over it then add a layer of refried beans.
Top with sour cream, sprinkle on half of the cheese, add another layer of tortillas.
Spread on remaining taco sauce and cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in a 375° preheated oven for 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for another 5 minutes or until top is brown.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Mix corn and milk and bring to a boil.
Separate corn from milk and return milk to fire.
Make paste from margarine and flour, adding the paste to milk to thicken.
Simmer 5 minutes and add salt and sugar.
Return corn to milk and bring back to a boil over low heat.
Transfer creamed corn to casserole dish.
Sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese.
Dot top with melted margarine
and brown under broiler.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except barbecue sauce.
Shape into loaf.
Put into crock-pot.
Cook on low for 5 to 6 hours; 10 or 15 minutes before serving, cover well with barbecue sauce.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for a few minutes.
(You can beat with a mixer instead.)
Pour into a greased 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with coconut and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot caramel sauce
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, 3 tablespoons butter and 1/2 cup cream in saucepan.
Bring to boil; gradually add remaining cream and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, just to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add salt and vanilla extract. Serve warm.
May be reheated.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend together with hand mixer liquid butter, sugar, Egg Beaters and vanilla.
Alternate, adding a little flour and then a little milk.
Keep alternating until you have added all the flour and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Stir in all but 1 teaspoon eggs then stir in jar of sauce.
Pour into pan, sprinkle with Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Top with crescent rolls.
Brush the rolls with remaining eggs.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in water.
Heat cottage cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and salt until warm, not hot.
Combine flour and soda in a large bowl.
Add heated mixture and eggs.
Knead until thoroughly mixed.
Let rise until double.
Punch down. Shape into 2-inch balls and place 1 inch apart in a greased pan. Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef-bean-biscuit casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix beans, barbecue sauce and brown sugar into beef.
Place in casserole dish.
Cut biscuits into half and place on top.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: quick swiss pie
directions: Press rolls into 12-inch pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix in oregano and spread over crust.
Beat cottage cheese, eggs and seasonings.
Spoon over meat.
Top with green pepper, tomato and cheese.
Bake at 370° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger meal in a dish
directions: Cook beef and onion in skillet until browned, stirring to crumble beef.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes. Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine cornmeal and flour; mix well.
Add egg, buttermilk and bacon drippings to cornmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon cornmeal mixture evenly over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In large bowl, combine all-purpose flour, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; stir in peaches and toss to coat well.
Set aside.
Mix 1 cup sugar in self-rising flour.
Add milk gradually until well blended.
Add melted butter; stir.
Pour 1/3 batter into baking dish.
Place peaches on top.
Spoon rest of batter on top of fruit.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Can be topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pepper steak
directions: Put green pepper slices, onion slices, steak cubes and garlic salt into large skillet with lid or electric skillet in a little oil.
Cook 10 minutes, slow with lid on.
Add the rest of the ingredients except noodles.
Cook, covered, until meat is done, about 2 hours.
When meat is almost done, cook noodles according to directions on package.
When noodles are done, drain well.
Serve meat and vegetable mixture over noodles.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat and onion.
Melt cheese over low heat.
Add sour cream, soup and chilies.
Soften 12 flour tortillas in oil. Place beef in each tortilla and roll up.
Lay in baking dish. Pour sauce over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: honey-almond dip
directions: Whisk ingredients together in a small bowl.
Makes about 3/4 cup of dip.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Put both kinds of bread in large mixing bowl.
Pour 1 cup water over bread and let soak for several minutes.
Mash very fine with fork.
Add the meat, chopped onion, parsley, grated cheese, slightly beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Mix and shape into loaf. Put lots of butter or margarine over top and bake 30 minutes. Pour tomato sauce over meat; sprinkle with oregano and continue baking 20 minutes longer.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Lightly grease baking dish large enough to hold pork chops (approximately 7 x 11-inch or 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch).
Put apples in bottom of baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Place chops on top.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour at 350°.
Do not overcook.

title: marsha's beef burgundy
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes; flour and brown in butter or margarine.
Add wine, consomme, salt and pepper, bay leaves, parsley and sliced onions. Simmer 1 1/2 hours (can be held overnight).
Add small onions and mushrooms.
Simmer 1/2 to 1 1/2 hours longer.
Serve with rice.
Meat may be treated with meat tenderizer if desired.
Serves 8.

title: weight watchers orange salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over Cool Whip.
Fold in.
Add oranges and pineapple to cottage cheese.
Fold Jell-O mixture into cottage cheese.
Let set overnight to congeal.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds and membrane from peppers.
Combine peppers and onion in food processor.
Sprinkle with salt (draws out liquid and bitterness).
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain well.
Discard liquid. Add vinegar and sugar to pulp.
Also add a couple drops of food coloring (optional).
Simmer until thick as for jam, 30 to 40 minutes.
Add pectin if needed.
Sterilize jars; fill with warm jelly.
Let cool.
Seal with wax.
Good served on crackers.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut
each
breast
into
8 nuggets about
square inches.
Combine bread
crumbs, cheese, Accent, salt and basil. Dip nuggets in melted
butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place in single layer on foil lined	baking	sheet.	Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: muddy buddys
directions: Pour Chex in a large bowl; set aside.
Mix together (in a saucepan) the chocolate chips, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla; then heat until melts.
Pour chocolate mixture over Chex cereal until well coated.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Unroll and press on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake as directed (not too long).
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread cream cheese mixture on cooled crescent rolls.
Spread vegetables on top of mixture.
Makes 1 cookie sheet full.

title: creamy peach pie(diabetic)
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in ice cream until melted.
Add whipped topping and mix well. Fold in peaches. Pour in pastry shell. Chill until firm.

title: eezey lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Let cool.
Add ice cream, cherries, pineapple and walnuts and pour in mold or dish.

title: peanut butter and butterscotch bits
directions: Melt together the peanut butter and butterscotch bits over low heat.
Stir in the cereal and drop in spoonfuls on a cookie sheet. Let cool in refrigerator.

title: no crust pizza
directions: Drain mushrooms; reserve liquid.
Add water to equal 1/3 cup liquid.
Combine the liquid, egg, crumbs, oregano, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; let stand 5 minutes.
Add beef; mix well. Pat beef mixture into 9-inch pie plate to form crust.
Cut cheese into 8 triangles; layer half atop beef mixture.
Top with pizza sauce, mushrooms, onions and green pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese; bake 5 minutes.
Remove to serving platter, using 2 spatulas.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked beans (easy)
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer for 8 hours.
Fry bacon strips and add to baked beans 1/2 hour before cooking time is ended.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix blueberries and sugar and set aside.
Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Fold in berries.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours and serve.

title: gourmet chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in greased baking dish.
Cover chicken pieces with Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and milk and spread over cheese.
Mix butter and Pepperidge Farm dressing and spread over soup.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: 3 hour beef
directions: Stir all ingredients together in roaster pan and cook, covered, at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: strawberry creamsicle
directions: Mix in blender with ice or ice cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make sure broccoli is well drained.
A salad spinner works great.
Mix broccoli with onion, bacon, sunflower seeds and raisins.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar together; add to broccoli mixture and chill.

title: strawberry frozen
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together. Add strawberries, pineapple, Cool Whip, bananas and walnuts.
Mix all together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze overnight.
Leave set a few minutes before cutting.
Tastes like ice cream.

title: egg and sausage dish
directions: Prepare overnight.
Combine eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard. Layer bread, cheese and sausage in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Mix in bowl vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Put layer of crumbs in crust; reserve small amount for topping.
Layer pudding mix over crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with reserved crumb mix.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Lightly butter a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Line with wax paper; lightly butter wax paper.
In a heavy, 3-quart saucepan, cook the brown sugar, granulated sugar and cream over low heat, stirring constantly with wooden spoon, until the sugar dissolves and the mixture comes to boiling.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until candy thermometer registers 234° or until a little in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter; set aside, without stirring, to cool to lukewarm (110°).
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
With wooden spoon, beat until thick and creamy. Stir in nuts.
Quickly turn into prepared pan; cool completely. Refrigerate.
Turn out of pan in one piece.
Remove waxed paper. With sharp knife, cut into pieces.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: swiss fondue
directions: Rub inside of fondue pot or saucepan with cut edge of garlic, then discard. In fondue pot, simmer wine. Blend in soup. Combine cheese and cornstarch, stir into soup mixture. Heat until cheese melts; stir now and then. Spear bread with fondue forks and dip into fondue. Makes about 4 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Using a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of sliced potatoes and onion until desired amount.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushroom soup and milk.
Top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake for approximately 1 hour.
This is a quick and delicious dish to serve with any meat.
Usually served with meat loaf or steak.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl at medium speed, cream butter, oil and both sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla, continue beating.
Add dry ingredients and stir until mixed.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls, roll in sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until very light brown.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually blend in flour mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes. Remove from pans; cool completely.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Steam vegetables until just tender-crisp (approximately 5 minutes for carrots and broccoli and 3 minutes for zucchini). Place in large bowl.
Add macaroni and onions and toss gently.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt, Parmesan cheese, olive oil, pepper, basil, oregano and garlic powder.
Add vegetable mixture.
Toss gently until well mixed.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: marybeth's dirt
directions: Cream together the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Then stir in the pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Put one layer of crushed cookies on bottom of dish.
Spread layer of creamed mixture on top, then alternately layer cookies and creamed mixture, ending with cookies on top.

title: schooner chocolate chips
directions: Chop all the nuts and mix together.
Cream butter, sugar, vanilla, Tia Maria and Frangelico until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Gradually beat into creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for approximately 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly; remove and serve.
Don't overbake.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: tomato dill pasta
directions: Drain off some of the juice from the tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients except the noodles in a large bowl.
Marinate at room temperature at least 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add hot pasta to sauce and toss.
Serve immediately.

title: summer squash delight
directions: Saute vegetables in butter for 3 minutes.
Add seasonings, cover and simmer until tender.
Remove lid from sauce pan, sprinkle with cheese, return lid and turn off heat.
Allow cheese to melt.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry crisscross square
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add salt, cinnamon and flour.
Work together as for pie dough pastry.
Add sour cream and baking soda mixture and add egg yolks.
Make a soft dough.
Spread in bottom of a cookie sheet pan leaving enough dough for crisscross topping. Brush top with egg, beaten.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Debone and chop.
Add chopped eggs, pickles and celery.
Add mayonnaise to desired spreading consistency.
Spread on favorite bread and top with olive.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine margarine and sugar until creamy. Add egg.
Mix these ingredients with flour, baking powder, soda, vanilla and milk.
Roll out 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix and put in large bowl coated with
corn oil; turn dough to coat with oil.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let set for 12 hours. Punch down dough.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Knead each part for 30 seconds or so.
Place into 3 sprayed with Pam loaf pans.
Cover with damp cloth; let set for 12 hours.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
After turning your bread from pans while warm, spread butter over the top of your bread.

title: tortilla tucks
directions: Spread each tortilla with a layer of cream cheese.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese, salsa, green onions, olives and avocado layer.
Roll up as tightly as possible and place seam side down in a flat dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 8 to 24 hours.
To serve, slice in 1 inch rounds.

title: black forest trifle
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions but add the egg yolks.
Set aside to cool completely.
Cut cake into 1-inch cubes (may not need the whole cake).

Using a large, deep bowl, layer cake, sprinkle pineapple juice, chocolate pudding, pie filling and Cool Whip, using about 1/3 of the amounts for each layer. Continue layering until bowl is full, but ending with Cool Whip. Garnish with chocolate curls or chips or cherries.
Refrigerate until served.
(Best chilled overnight.)
Spoon into dessert dishes.

title: no bake peanut butter cups
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and melted margarine until thoroughly mixed together.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips together in pan or microwave.
Spread over crust and chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in milk, spices, vinegar, nuts, and vanilla.
Boil raisins in enough water to cover them for approximately 5 minutes.
Drain and add to pie mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° or until pie is firm.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: kanelkakor(swedish cinnamon cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and almond extract.
Add flour mixed with baking powder and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Shape dough into 4 logs.
Place on Teflon cookie sheets (17 x 14-inch).
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with chopped almonds.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Let cool for 15 minutes and cut into diagonal 1-inch pieces (sprinkle with chopped almonds) and return to oven. Turn oven off and leave to dry and cool.

title: festive chicken salad
directions: Mix and chill.
May be shaped* and decorated with green pepper, olives, etc. for serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: form a circle chicken
directions: Saute green onions, mushrooms and garlic in the butter. Remove from
pan
or
use
a separate skillet.
Debone chicken breasts and put
a slice of Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Roll up both halves.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven, spread 1 can of soup on
the bottom.
Put
the breast halves in the middle and use the
rest of
the
chicken
parts to form a circle around the breasts.
Top other
pieces of chicken with a slice of cheese and
top
with the mushroom sauce.
Carefully spread the last can of soup over the top.
Put on lid and bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with a baked potato, French bread and green salad.

title: brandied chocolate fondue
directions: Combine chocolate and water in small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring often, until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth. Add whipping cream and remaining ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Serve warm with fresh strawberries.
Yields 2/3 cup.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly margarine, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Then add remaining ingredients, but pie filling. Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Make a hole in the center of cookie and put in a little bit of pie filling.
Can be made without pie filling.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Refrigerate overnight. Next morning, let stand 30 minutes.
Put crumbled potato chips over top and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 people.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Soak the raisins overnight in hot water.
Drain.
Blend sugar, flour, milk and salt.
Add 3 egg yolks and raisins and cook until creamy. Pour into baked pie crust and cover with meringue.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Season, stew, cool and shred chuck roast. Dice and brown onion. Add rest of ingredients. Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Add shredded beef. Mix well. Serve on toasted buns. Serves 12.

title: cheesy apple pie
directions: In one bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine next 5 ingredients; set aside.
For cheesy pastry shell, combine and mix with pastry blender the rest of ingredients, except cold water.
Sprinkle water (3 to 4 tablespoons) over dry ingredients.
Roll into pie crust for a 9-inch shell.
Put apple mixture in shell, then sprinkle cheese mixture over that.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then lower to 350° for 25 minutes longer.

title: posey chow-chow
directions: Use spices to taste: cloves, turmeric and allspice.

title: cheese grits
directions: Prepare grits as on package. Add butter and cheese to hot grits. Crack 2 eggs into measuring cup. Fill with half and half to make 1 cup. Beat mixture. Combine with grits. Pour into greased casserole. Cover with crushed cereal or bread crumbs tossed with melted butter. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: foil wrapped dinner
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut meat into 1-inch pieces.
Place frozen peas in colander or sieve.
Run cold water over peas, just until broken apart.
Drain.

title: pretty pumpkin 4-layer torte
directions: Mix cake mix, pumpkin, soda, eggs and water together.
Bake in 2 circular cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and split each half to make 4 layers.

title: brownies
directions: Grease an 8-inch pan and line with wax paper.
Melt together unsweetened chocolate and shortening.
Beat eggs well and add sugar gradually.
Beat in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add chopped nuts, if desired. Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
(Don't overbake if you like them "chewy".) Invert pan on cake rack and cool.
Peel off wax paper.

title: quiche florentine
directions: In large bowl, combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Over top of cake mix, sprinkle chopped rhubarb.
Sprinkle sugar over rhubarb and pour 1 pint whipping cream over top of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, or until done.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in a saucepan. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and rolled oats and stir well.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: turkey chili
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in hot oil until onion is soft; stir in turkey.
Cook until no longer pink.
Add tomatoes, soy sauce, garlic and chili powder.
Stir to combine.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in beans; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes more.
Serve over rice if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: south of the border dip
directions: In large skillet, saute onions in margarine.
Reduce heat to low.
Add remaining ingredients; stir slowly until process cheese spread is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and put in a buttered casserole dish (long pan).

title: georgia caviar
directions: Peel outer skin off large Vidalia onion.
Cut onion from top into 8 to 16 sections being sure not to cut all the way through root end.

title: avocado salad
directions: Cut the avocado into halves or in slices.
Alternate slices of orange or pineapple with avocado.
Plain lemon juice may be squeezed on avocado.
Serve with French dressing or with thin mayonnaise.

title: loaf cake(eggless and butterless)
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water.
When done, add cold water to remaining ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: savory chicken or turkey squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 5 teaspoons margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 squares or rectangles and seal perforations. Spoon 1/2 cup of meat mixture onto center of each rectangle. Pull 4 corners of dough to top and seal.
Brush with the 3 teaspoons margarine and dip into the crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain juice off beets.
Stir beets into Cool Whip and chill.

title: the ultimate chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Mix first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat next 3 ingredients.
At low speed, beat in mayonnaise.
Add flour mixture alternately with water.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and set aside.
Fry noodles in hot oil (only takes seconds) a little at a time (noodles will puff up).
Cut up chicken in thin strips.
Cut up lettuce in strips.
Mix chicken and lettuce well.
Pour mixture over all and mix.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Chop onions and brown until golden in butter.
Cut zucchini in chunks and stir into onions.
In another pot, boil broth.
Add broth to onions and zucchini. Add vinegar and dill to zucchini broth and bring to a boil.
Sprinkle in farina and lower heat. Simmer 20 minutes, covered.
Add a little water if too thick.
Put soup in blender and mix until creamy.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: cherry fizz
directions: Combine cherry preserves and water.
Pour cherry mixture into 2 tall glasses.
Add scoops of cherry nut/or vanilla ice cream. Slowly pour carbonated beverage down sides of glasses.
Makes 2 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Pour into 8-inch skillet or pan of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix milk and cereal together and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine and spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: bubba's beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in a baking dish.
Combine all ingredients, except barbecue sauce, and pour over brisket.
Cover pan tightly. Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Top with desired amount of barbecue sauce and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli in one can of chicken broth and set aside.
Melt oleo and stir in flour in a soup pot.
Add other 3 cans of chicken broth to oleo/flour and simmer until thickens.
Add broccoli-broth mixture and evaporated milk.
Add Cheez Whiz and melt.

title: chick'n chiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken, 1 cup cheese and chilies. Set aside.
In pan, combine soup, sour cream and cumin; heat until warm.
Do not boil.
Stir 1 cup sauce into chicken mixture. Divide chicken mixture among tortillas.
Roll up tortillas and place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until cheese is melted and sauce is bubbly.

title: fajita shish kabob marinade
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place meat in pan with high sides or large bowl, covering with marinade.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours, turning meat frequently.
For moist meat, cover grill with aluminum foil with holes punched at regular intervals.
