title: hot spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain well. Combine with other ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Chill several hours.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 36.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Add enough milk to make soft dough.
Knead lightly. Roll 3/4-inch thick on a lightly floured board.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Bake at 400° on ungreased sheet 20 minutes or until brown.
Makes 15 biscuits.

title: chocolate cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Blend cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Combine and beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips and set aside. Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, cocoa, soda and 1 teaspoon salt. Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Fill cups 1/3 full with chocolate batter.
Top each with a heaping teaspoon of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and chopped or slivered almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: busy day chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan. Cover bottom evenly with rice. Arrange chicken pieces on rice. Dot with butter. Sprinkle dry onion soup over all. Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour boiling water into pan. Bake for about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin scones
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and mix well.
Stir in pumpkin.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Knead lightly.
Roll out on lightly floured surface and cut with biscuit or cookie cutter.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, oleo and coffee; add egg, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until almost no indentation remains when touched, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix together water, sugar and yeast.
Add flour, oil and salt. Knead a little and put in "oiled" bowl.
Let rise.
Spread on greased pizza pan (can fill 2 small pans).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: black bean and rice casserole
directions: Layer in a deep casserole dish: rice, 1/2 salsa, 1/2 cheese, beans, salsa, cheese. Heat thoroughly at 350° for 25 minutes. Garnish with sour cream and scallions.

title: corn, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Stir corn, rice and cheese.
In bowl, beat eggs, salt, pepper and milk.
Place corn mix in dish; pour eggs mix over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown scrambled sausage.
Drain and wash.
Add Velveeta and chili; mix together.
Put bowl of mixture in microwave to melt cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spicy italian roast(crock-pot)
directions: Season the roast with the garlic salt and place it in the Crock-Pot.
Add the mushrooms and onion.
Combine the seasoning mix with the tomato sauce and pour it over everything in the Crock-Pot.
Cover and cook on Low 10-12 hours (high for 4-6 hours).
To thicken gravy, make a paste of the melted butter, flour and tomato paste, and stir into the meat drippings in the Crock-Pot.
Cover and cook on High approximately 30 minutes or until thickened.
Serve over hot pasta or rice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put the pumpkin into one large mixing bowl.
In another smaller mixing bowl, beat 6 eggs.
Pour beaten eggs into large mixing bowl and blend with pumpkin. Blend in 2 cups sugar. Blend in 2 1/2 cups milk.
Mix the 3 teaspoons of cornstarch into the remaining 1/2 cup of milk and blend this into the large bowl. Blend in 2 teaspoons of pumpkin pie spice and 1 1/2 teaspoons of nutmeg.
Pour completed mix into 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 50 to 55 minutes.
(Shake pies lightly; if the pumpkin mix is firm like Jell-O in the center and not watery, the pie is done.)
Make two 9-inch pies.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and coconut extract; beat well.
Stir in SpudFlakes and Bix-Mix.
Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls; arrange 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: lima beans in mustard sauce
directions: Cook beans and drain.
Heat salad dressing, milk and mustard, stirring constantly.
Turn hot beans into serving dish.
Pour hot sauce over beans.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: sugar-free peanut butter cookies
directions: Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350°.

title: sunday dinner roast
directions: Place roast on heavy-duty foil.
Spread roast with undiluted mushroom soup.
Sprinkle over it the dry onion soup mix.
Wrap, sealing well.
Use a shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.
Makes delicious gravy for potatoes or rice.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and baking powder; set aside.
Cream Crisco and sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flavorings.
Add flour and sour cream alternately, beginning and ending with flour.

title: taco surprise
directions: Prepare the stuffing as directed on box.
Set aside.
Brown meat and add sauce.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Layer half of stuffing in casserole.
Top with ground beef, then spread cheese over meat.
Cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
You can sprinkle cheese on top also.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Brown ground beef with onion and peppers; drain. Add both cans of soup to meat mixture. Add cooked noodles; stir well. Place in a casserole dish and top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Add chunks of butter to corn and salt and pepper to taste. Add canned milk and cracker crumbs; mix well.
Turn mixture into a buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: whole wheat buttermilk rolls
directions: Mix yeast, buttermilk, sugar, salt and egg in mixer bowl.
Beat until all are mixed well.
Add Crisco and potatoes; beat well.
Add flour and beat well.
Cover and let rise.
Push down; form rolls and let rise.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: candied fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands in a large bowl.
Grease 2 loaf pans, then line with brown paper (grocery bag).
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
When done, brush top and sides with white Karo syrup.

title: broccoli salad]
directions: Soak broccoli in salt water for several hours.
Drain.
Mix altogether.
Serves 6.

title: corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups. Blend all ingredients about 20 seconds.
Beat 1 minute.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes; immediately remove from pan.

title: pico de gallo(rooster's beak)
directions: Cut tomatoes and cucumbers into small cubes.
Chop the onion and cilantro leaves.
Mince the jalapenos.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients together and pour into crust. Chill.

title: baked bologna
directions: With sharp knife, cut skin of bologna. Cut into 1/2-inch or more diamond shapes.
Punch holes all the way through so the basting gets in all the meat. Baste generously with brown sugar and pineapple or use any kind of jelly to suit taste.

Bake in oven until piping hot all the way through, or if you prefer, put on rotisserie and use barbecue sauce instead of brown sugar. Baste every 15 minutes for a barbecue flavor. Delicious either way.

title: cream peas and potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender. Cook peas in separate pan, add sugar. Melt butter in pan, add flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in milk. Cook until thick. Drain potatoes and peas and place in bowl. Pour sauce over and stir to coat.

title: yogurt rice sauce
directions: Cook rice.
In another saucepan, add well beaten egg to yogurt.
Stir well and cook on low fire.
Stir until mixture boils.
Add rice.
Cook 5 more minutes.

title: creamy lemon cheese cake
directions: Measure 1 cup dry cake mix; set aside.
Combine remaining mix with 1 egg and oil.
Press in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger skouse
directions: Brown meat in large pan or pot.
Drain meat.
Meat can be rinsed with cool water if less fat is desired.
Put all ingredients in pot and simmer until potatoes are done, stirring occasionally.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in a microwave-safe bowl.
Cook in microwave for 10 minutes.
Do not cover.
Cool in water while mixing.
Then pour into greased pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Keep in fridge.

title: chocoholic brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Watch for brownies to slightly pull away from sides of pan.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
These brownies are very rich and dense.
You might want a gallon of fresh milk to go along with them!

title: chart house dip
directions: Blend ingredients well.
It helps to soften cream cheese first.
Serve with cut-up veggies or crackers.
Can sprinkle with paprika for color!
This recipe is served in the Chart House Restaurant in Vail, Colorado.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together. Add cinnamon and sugar. Beat the eggs and remaining ingredients.
Mix but do not beat. Makes 2 large loaves or several muffins. Bake 1 hour at 350° for loaves, less time for muffins.

title: mocha walnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup of morsels over hot water. Stir until smooth; cool to room temperature.
In small cup dissolve coffee in 2 teaspoons boiling water.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl combine butter, sugars and coffee.
Beat until creamy.
Add egg and melted morsels.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in walnuts and remaining morsels.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to cool 2 to 3 minutes before removing.
Yields 24 (3-inch) cookies.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix the meatball mixture together and form meatballs.
Melt 1 1/2 tablespoons shortening in large skillet.
Cook meatballs and remove from skillet.
Pour shortening from skillet.

title: snack in a bag
directions: Combine oat circles breakfast cereal, dried apricot halves (chopped), raisins, chopped pitted dates, sunflower seeds and almonds.
This snack has been scientifically proven to help PMS symptoms! Really!
Divide into 3 plastic bags.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, salt, cinnamon, sugars and oil; mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup of this mixture.
Add nuts and cinnamon to this mixture; set aside.
Add baking powder, soda, egg and buttermilk to mixture in bowl; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with reserved mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: au gratin potato casserole(texas-style)
directions: Mix 1 cup melted butter, salt and pepper; add onion and saute. Add soup, sour cream, cheese and potatoes; mix well.
Place in a large greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inches).
Melt 1/2 stick butter and add cornflakes; mix well.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: cold cuts quiche
directions: Spread crescent rolls on bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place 2 layers of salami, ham and American cheese.
Drain 1 jar Progresso pepper salad and place over the layers.
Repeat layers in reverse; cheese, ham and salami.
Top with more crescent rolls.
Pour 2 beaten eggs over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Blend together cream cheese, yogurt and sugar.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Spoon into 6 paper muffin cups in muffin pan. Cover and freeze until firm.
Remove paper cups from salads and arrange on lettuce leaves and top with chopped nuts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti with mushrooms
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Cook and stir mushrooms in butter in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until tender.

title: marinade sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together and use with beef, chicken or fish.
Marinate in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours, occasionally turning the meat over several times.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add flour, beaten eggs, vanilla, nuts and morsels.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased (or Pam sprayed) pan at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse(josh thacker's favorite dessert)
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix flour, melted butter and 1 1/2 cups pecans together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool.

title: english toffee cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix.
Add vanilla and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Mix well.
Press dough in greased tin (10 x 15-inch).
Spread egg white over dough in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes.
Cut cookies while warm.
Makes three dozen.

title: sinful caramel pie
directions: Brown coconut and almonds in margarine. Set aside.
Mix other ingredients.
If needed, add a little milk.
Pour into 2 crusts and sprinkle top with nuts and coconut.
You can warm caramel in microwave a few minutes and drizzle easier. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: zucchini pie(tastes like apple)
directions: Peel and remove seeds and chop or slice zucchini like apples. Put in kettle with 1/4 cup water.
Simmer until tender.
Drain; cool.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Fill 9-inch
unbaked pie shell; top with crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes. Large, oversized zucchini work best.
Absolutely delicious.

title: lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and 1 cup water in a small saucepan.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 to 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and cool completely.

title: pineapple delight salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: julie moonan dessert pudding
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch cooking dish with graham crackers. Put chocolate pudding on top of graham crackers.
Slice bananas, then next layer of graham crackers, the pudding (vanilla), then crushed graham crackers on top.
Chill for 1 hour, ready to serve.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, grapes, apples and nuts. Add pineapple and sugar; stir. Refrigerate 3 hours. Add marshmallows and fold in whipped cream 30 minutes before serving.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Drain and save 1 cup of broth.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Saute onion and cut cheese into cubes.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Divide pastry almost in half.
Roll out larger half on floured surface to 13-inch circle.
Line 9-inch plate with pastry.
Trim pastry to 1/2 inch beyond rim of pie plate.
Combine tomatoes, sugar, flour, lemon juice, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in bowl; mix well.
Arrange tomato mixture in pastry-lined pie plate.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour water over dates; add soda and let cool.
Cream eggs, shortening and sugar.
Add date mixture.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Before baking, top with chocolate chips, sugar and nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package and cool.
Line the bottom of pan with 12 cookies.
Top with 1 banana, sliced.
Spread half the pudding on top.
Top with remaining cookies, then with 1 banana, sliced and remaining pudding.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pecan bars
directions: In a small bowl, mix well flour and 2 tablespoons brown sugar. With pastry blender, work in oleo until dough holds together. Press on bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until firm.

title: orange flip
directions: Combine juices and chill.
Add mineral water and ice (if desired) just before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion and drain.
Add potatoes, tomatoes, tomato sauce and Veg-All.
Cover and cook until potatoes are done, about 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: deep fried ice cream
directions: Roll ice cream into balls and refreeze.
Heat oil until hot. Crush corn flakes and roll ice cream balls in corn flakes until well covered.
One at a time, place balls on slotted spoon and dip into oil.
(Do not drop off spoon.) Leave in oil until corn flakes are browned, about 2 to 3 seconds.
Roll in cinnamon sugar and place in serving dish.
Drizzle with honey, top with whipped cream and serve.
One ball per serving.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Mix and boil first 4 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pecans, Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Cool and shape into balls, then roll in coconut.

title: old-timey potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until translucent.
Add potatoes, water and salt and cook until tender.
Add milk and season to taste. Simmer a few minutes before serving.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Mix ingredients in order given and pour
into a well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for about 1 hour.
Cool well before removing cake from pan.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 475°
until done.

title: fudgy chocolate cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
In saucepan, melt "1 cup" chips with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour over crust; top with nuts and remaining chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 20 minutes or until set.
Cool. Cut into bars.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger lightly with onion.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer meat first.
Spread 2 cans of cream of chicken; don't add water. Add grated cheese on top, then layer Tots on top.
Bake 25 minutes or until Tots are brown at 325°.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and sugar and make 3 "wells" in bowl.
In one put soda, in one put vinegar and in one put oil.
Pour water over all and mix.
You can also add a pinch of salt and a beaten egg if you wish.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes or make 30 cupcakes.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Heat milk in top of double boiler, then add cheese and stir until melted.
Cool and then add other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: mad hatter meatballs
directions: Brown green pepper and onion in margarine.
Stir in rice soup, tomato soup and water.
Form meatballs from remaining ingredients. Drop into sauce.
Simmer, covered, on low for 1 hour.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 15 minutes or until thick.
Great served with mashed potatoes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine everything except crabmeat.
Stir well.
Add crab meat. Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: the ultimate eggnog
directions: Separate eggs and stir yolks with whiskey or rum, 2 cups of sugar and 1 teaspoon nutmeg.
Let mixture "ripen" in refrigerator 12 to 24 hours.
Just before serving, add half and half to mixture.
Beat egg whites, adding remaining 1 cup sugar while beating; beat until sugar is dissolved and whites are firm.
In separate bowl, whip cream.
Fold egg whites and whipped cream into yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 25.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix equal amounts of Coke and ketchup in a large pot.
Add chicken (skin, if preferred).
Let come to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until done, approximately 45 minutes to one hour.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in water (set aside).
Pour soup in pot.
Do not add water.
Heat to boiling. Add cream cheese in soup.
Stir until melted.
Add celery and green onions.
Cook 5 minutes. Add shrimp and mayonnaise.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add dash of salt (Tony's seasoning, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder to taste).
Pour gelatine into pot with soup and other ingredients.
Mix.
Pour into greased mold.
Chill for 3 hours or overnight.

title: pizza with smoked mozzarella and dried tomatoes
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, prepare Sicilian Pizza Dough.

title: snicker cake
directions: Make cake as directed on package.
Pour half of batter in large greased pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, milk and margarine over low heat.
Pour caramel mixture over cake. Mix chocolate chips and nuts, sprinkle onto caramel mixture. Then smooth rest of the cake batter over this mixture.
Lower oven to 200°; bake 10 minutes, then increase to 350° and bake until done.

title: red hot wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips.
Pat dry.
Deep fry until done (brown and crispy) or bake at 425° for 1 hour, turning halfway through cooking time.
Combine red hot sauce, oleo and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip wings in sauce to completely coat. Serve with favorite dip.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill. Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with raw vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: coal garden
directions: Mix water, salt, bluing liquid and ammonia.
Pour over coal in a pie pan or glass container.
Drop food coloring on the coal and mixture.
Different colors make it look pretty.
Grows best where it is warm and dry.
To keep it growing, carefully add more liquid from the sides of the coal.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Open cans of green beans.
Pour out liquid from 1 can and reserve the liquid from the other can.
Fry bacon until crisp; reserve drippings.
Crumble the bacon; saute the onion in bacon drippings.
Stir in flour, liquid from beans, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add the drained green beans and crumbled bacon.
Heat until warmed through.

title: cinnamon almond bars
directions: Will need a jelly roll pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread 1/2 of potatoes in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Slice sausage link and spread evenly on potatoes.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread on sausage. Cover and bake for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 10 additional minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place bread in casserole dish.
Mix chicken, vegetables, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; spread over bread.
Mix eggs, milk and oleo.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Take out to bake. Spread the chicken soup over top, then top with the cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Remove from oven and top with shredded cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Mix and spread thinly in an oiled pan.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Layer crackers (not crumbs) in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare pudding with 3 cups milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over crackers. Put another layer of crackers on top of pudding mixture.
Melt chocolate frosting in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and swirl over crackers.
Refrigerate for
2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cook vanilla pudding as directed on package.
Mix jello and pudding, refrigerate overnight.
Whip cream.
Beat pudding mixture, add whipped cream, fruit, cherries and marshmallows.
Mix thoroughly, chill before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried grits with ham
directions: In saucepan, combine 4 cups water and salt.
Bring to boiling. Slowly stir in grits.
Cook, covered, over low heat for 2 1/2 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.
Stir in ham and margarine.
Pour into
a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cool. Chill until firm, about 3 hours.

Cut in 2-inch squares. Beat egg with 2 tablespoons cold water. Dip squares in egg mixture, then in flour. In skillet, cook grit squares on both sides in small amount of hot shortening until golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve with maple flavored syrup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: southern pie crust
directions: Blend ingredients with electric mixer.
Add ice water, 3 tablespoons at a time.
Blend in until all water is added.
Blend to smooth.
Take out on a floured pastry board or sheet.
Roll out in 7-inch pie crust.
Makes 2.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese soup
directions: Stir soup until smooth.
Add milk and pepper.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, onions, sauce and cheese.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Toss first 3 ingredients in salad bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour over cabbage and mix in well. Serve immediately.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine flour,

salt and pepper. Roll meat in this mixture. Brown meat in the shortening. Add tomatoes, tomato soup and water; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring now and then. Add onions, carrots and potatoes. Cook until vegetables are tender. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes to thicken.

title: inside-out chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when completely cooled.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
While hot, cut up cheeses and mix together.
Mix egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Put all together and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Beat cream cheese in large mixer bowl until creamy.
Add 3 ounces smoked salmon, coarsely chopped, and beat at low speed until blended. Add minced onion, mayonnaise, yellow mustard and minced garlic.
Beat at high speed until well blended.
Serve with crackers or breadsticks.
Makes 2 cups.

title: care and feeding of "herman"
directions: In a large bowl, feed Herman 1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup flour and 1 cup milk.
Stir thoroughly.
From now on, refrigerate.

title: nathan's steak
directions: Get some meat and cook it in a pan and put the fire on the pan and it cooks up.
Then you have steak.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frypan, adding salt and pepper; drain. Add stewed tomatoes and mix well. Cut processed cheese into small chunks; add to meat mixture and melt. Add enchilada sauce to meat mixture, mixing well. Set aside. Cut cream cheese into 8 equal blocks. Spread block of cheese over 1/2 of each tortilla. Spread light layer of green chiles over cheese. Fold in half. Set aside. Spray 13 x 9-inch bread pan lightly with cooking spray. Layer bottom of pan with tortilla chips. Pour 1/2 of meat mixture over chips. Place folded tortillas over layer of meat mixture. Pour remainder of meat mixture over folded tortillas. Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 20 minutes. Remove from oven and spread grated cheese on top. Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute vegetables in skillet with small amount of oil.
Boil chicken and remove.
Dice and return diced chicken to broth.
Pour vegetables into broth and continue boiling for a while.
Add chopped cilantro (3/4 to 1 cup).
Serve and top with fried tortillas, grated Mozzarella and add chopped avocado.

title: sugar thins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add remaining ingredients. Chill overnight.
Roll out very thin on floured board.
Cut and decorate.
Bake in greased cookie sheet at 350° for 5 minutes. Makes about 10 dozen.

title: garden stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, stir all ingredients except mushrooms.
Stuff each mushroom cap with 1 tablespoon of filling. Place in buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crumbs with margarine; press into a 10-inch pie pan. Saute onions in margarine.
Pour into crust.
Scald milk and add slowly to eggs.
Add grated cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Pour into crust and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into greased and floured 9
x
13-inch
pan.
Combine
powdered
sugar, 3 eggs, flavoring and softened cream cheese.
Mix well and spread over cake mix layer.
Bake
at
for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown the ground beef over medium-high heat.
Stir in the taco seasoning and tomatoes.
Line a 9 x 13 inch baking dish with half of the tortillas.
Spoon the beef mixture into the dish, then top with the remaining tortillas.
Spread salsa over the tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream the sugar and eggs. Add melted butter.
Add milk, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well. Bake at 325° until firm.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Before starting jelly, in quart jar, add 1 1/2 cups flour and fill jar with water. Shake to dissolve all lumps. In pan, combine peppers, mustard, salt, vinegar and sugar. Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly. Add flour mixture to thicken. Place in pint or quart jars.

title: chicken pie
directions: Add chicken to bottom pie crust.
Top with soup mixed with sour cream, salt and pepper.
Cover with top crust!
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until brown.
(This freezes well, bake when needed.)

title: baked alaska
directions: Bake any type of cake in a long pan.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer and place your favorite ice cream on top of cake.
Trim the cake down to 1 inch larger than the ice cream.
Cover with meringue or fluffy white frosting.

title: jelly pecan pie
directions: On medium speed, beat eggs in mixer.
Add sugar, jelly and margarine.
Stir in pecans and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Chill water and pineapple juice.
Add Seven-Up.
Make ice ring with Kool-Aid.
Makes 1 gallon.
Serves 25 (1/2 cups).

title: mexican fiesta biscuits mix
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in oven in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish or nonstick aluminum baking pan.
Tilt to evenly coat dish.

title: caramel nut fruit fudge
directions: In a saucepan, measure light brown sugar, margarine and evaporated milk.
Bring to boiling point.
Let boil 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and 1 cup 10x confectioners sugar.
Beat and add cherries, coconut, pecans and raisins.
This should harden quickly; cut into squares.

title: lawry's fiesta dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with tortilla chips or fresh cut vegetables, such as carrots.

title: whole wheat irish soda bread
directions: Mix ingredients; knead.
Make deep slits.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 450° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well; form balls.
Press with fork dipped in water. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bobby's chili
directions: Combine tomatoes and water; bring to boil.
Add onions, pepper, salt and garlic.
Mix well and bring to boil.
Add ground beef (uncooked), stirring constantly.
After coming to good boil, cover and simmer for 90 minutes.
Add water, if needed.
Add 4 1/2 tablespoons chili seasoning (Bobby uses Morton's).
Cover and simmer 60 minutes.
Add 2 cups mashed cooked pinto beans to tighten the chili (an old trick Bobby learned from an army cookbook).

title: rabbit with herbs and mushrooms
directions: Cut up the rabbit into serving size pieces.
Saute in butter until browned on all sides.
Mix parsley and chives with 2 tablespoons butter with a fork.
Sprinkle rabbit with flour, cook 1 minute while stirring.
Add wine, butter and herb mixture, 1 cup water, garlic, thyme, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 1 hour over low heat.
Add mushrooms and simmer about 10 more minutes.

title: fish chowder
directions: Place fish in a large skillet.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk, bay leaf, celery and thyme. Simmer 10 to 20 minutes. Remove skin and bone. Cut fish into 1/2-inch pieces. Strain liquid from fish and reserve for later.
In saucepan, melt butter. Saute onion.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat. Gradually add the liquid from the fish, then 4 cups milk and potatoes.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in cheese until melted. Add fish.
Heat and serve.
Serves 9.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil butter, cocoa and water.
Pour in large bowl; while hot, add flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Pour in large cookie sheet that has been greased and floured.
Spread evenly.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes (no longer).

title: fried onion rings
directions: Dip onions after sliced in a small bowl of milk, then dip in flour.
French fry until golden brown.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until just about done.
Peel and cube.
Add rest of ingredients and put crumbled bacon on the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar.
Roll in large marble size balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Keep cool.
Will keep well.

title: rolled enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add onions, seasoning mix, water and refried beans; mix well.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Spoon onto tortillas; roll to enclose filling.
Place seam side down in greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Mix taco sauce and tomato sauce in bowl.
Spoon over tortillas.
Sprinkle with 2 cups cheese.
Bake until cheese has melted.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.

title: tomato soup
directions: Chop tomatoes coarsely.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
